**Goal**: Next.js (App Router, TS) + Tailwind v4+ + **Leaflet** app for municipal risk layers in Guanajuato. **UI** modern, clean, fast; **mobile first**; **menus hidable**; **WCAG AA**.  
**Theme**: colors from sg.guanajuato.gob.mx; high contrast `#6580A4,#0066FF,#00A99D,#FF8200,#32AA00,#F45197,#B9C8E7`.

## Coding Rules
- Next.js App Router, React TS functional components.
- Tailwind v4 only; no custom CSS frameworks. Accessible components.
- Map: Leaflet; with openstreetmap; keep bundles light; memoize data joins; simple quantile choropleths.

## Tech & Repo
- Stack: Next.js 14+, TS strict, Tailwind v4+, shadcn/ui (light), **Leaflet + react-leaflet**.   

## Layout (wireframe → product)
- Desktop: **Left Sidebar (320px, collapsible)** “Capas de información” (search + grouped toggles) · **Map Canvas** fills rest · **Legend** floating bottom-right.  
- Mobile: sidebar hidden by default; **FABs**: *Capas* y *Periodo/Ajustes*; swipe-left open; ESC/tap-out close; 44px targets; focus-trap.  
- Shortcuts: `g`=Capas, `p`=Periodo, `l`=Leyenda.

## Coding Standards
- TS `strict`; no `any`. JSDoc on utils.  
- Tailwind v4 only; no custom CSS frameworks. Accessible components.

## Etiquette
- Ask only task-critical questions; otherwise make reversible assumptions.  
- When done, update @PLAN_MVP.md
